</s>
<s id="592:3">
Au-delà de ma personne, j'ai honte pour notre institution.
</s>
<s id="592:4">
Elle est engluée dans le politiquement correct.
</s>
<s id="592:5">
Il n'y a aucune confrontation des idées.
</s>
<s id="592:6">
Il n'y a aucune liberté véritable d'expression.
</s>
<s id="592:7">
C'est le conformisme.
</s>
<s id="592:8">
Nous passons notre temps à faire le travail que ferait bien mieux une agence, une agence technique d'harmonisation des normes ou des règles et, pour le reste, nous jouons à l'Organisation des Nations unies.
</s>
<s id="592:9">
Vous défendez les droits de l'homme au Guatemala, en Indonésie, partout dans le monde où nous dev- où vous n'avez aucune compétence.
</s>
<s id="592:10">
Vous n'êtes pas capables de défendre les droits d'un de vos membres.
</s>
<s id="592:11">
J'ai honte pour ce Parlement, c'est un Parlement minable et un Parlement de minables.
</s>
</interpreter>
</st>
</speaker>
</text>
<text id="594" date="2011-05-10" length="short" lengthw="131" duration="short" durations="59.0" speed="medium" speedwm="133.2" delivery="impromptu" topic="Procedure and Formalities" topicspec="Approval of the Minutes of the previous sitting" type="French spoken sources" comments="NA">
